{"questionId":"27206","questionHtml":"<p>Given that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/c229c74a0f153fcb6db7b307cb4a5f68394d3b1b.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for an increasing graph, entirely in first quadrant, becoming concave down for larger values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for tending towards the origin and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for asymptote labelled at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27206","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ2.4b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that limT→∞k=A and limT→0k=0, sketch the graph of k against T.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}